# One Bullet Extra - Zombie Survival Game

This is a simple zombie survival game called "One Bullet Extra" built using the Arcade library in Python. In this game, your objective is to survive as many rounds as possible against a horde of zombies by collecting ammo, health, and power-ups and scoring points by eliminating zombies. 

## How to Play
- Move left: Left Arrow Key (←)
- Move right: Right Arrow Key (→)
- Jump: Spacebar
- Shoot: Mouse Click
- Pick up items (bullets, apples, power-ups): E
- Pause/Unpause: ESC

## Game Rules
- Zombies take 3 hits to die.
- The player starts with 1 life and has a maximum of 5.
- Power-ups stack and can be unlocked with a score of 300 points.

## Controls
- Use the left and right arrow keys to move the player.
- Press the spacebar to make the player jump.
- Click with the mouse to shoot zombies.
- Use the "E" key to pick up items like bullets, apples, and power-ups.
- Press "ESC" to pause and unpause the game.

## Game Features
- You need to survive as many rounds as possible by defeating zombies.
- Collect ammo to reload your gun.
- Collect apples to gain extra lives.
- Unlock power-ups with a score of 300 points to enhance your abilities.

## Dependencies
This game uses the Arcade library and requires Pyglet.

